	quest.3A82EA792C344D06.quest_desc: [
		"The Idea of a generator regulator is simple:"
		"A device capable of taking the output of of my generator and keeping it at a certain output voltage, despite additional current draw from the generator."
		""
		"You might've noticed how as you pull more and more current from your generator, the output voltage becomes less and less. This is problematic as additional load on your generator may drop the outlet voltage in certain devices you run on the network, I mean, You wouldn't want your lights to dim 50% every time you run your basin heater dont you?"
		""
		"The setup would be placed after your generator. The basic idea, is that as you drop the output voltage of the generator, the servo rotates the variac, which has it's connectors set up to where it drops our generator voltage to some sort of standardized outlet voltage."
		""
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"1. The setup is somewhat simple, connect a transformer from the output of the generator to drop to ~45 V to power our servo."
		""
		"2. Take another transformer and drop the output of our generator down to 2.5V or another calibrated logic level voltage, then plug that into the signal (green) port of the servo."
		""
		"3. Place down the variac, connect primary to our generator and common to a shared ground, then attatch two chain drives to the generator, so that there is room to place a valve."
		""
		"4. Turn the valve until the variac outputs the standardized voltage you want to output."
		""
		"At this point, the servo should be on and at whatever signal it's calibrated to, and the variac should output the desired voltage."
		""
		"{@pagebreak}"
		""
		"From here, apply an artifical load to the network through a power resistor or another method. Monitor the output voltage of the variac as we apply more load. It should follow loosely around our desired voltage. If it strays too far for your liking, gently calibrate the signal transformers until a desireable output is reached."
		""
		"Regulators like this should be on the output of all generators on your power grid, in order to maintain a stable output voltage in our power lines."
	]
	quest.3A82EA792C344D06.quest_subtitle: "Build a simple generator regulator"
	quest.3A82EA792C344D06.title: "Yo Why Is My Outlet Voltage Over 800V?"
	quest.3ABBDBAD8B1A571B.quest_desc: [
