	quest.684CD724E2211165.quest_desc: [
		"In order to effectively transmit electricity across long distances, the electrical output of a generator must be hypercondensed into a high voltage through the use of a transformer. The parasitic resistance of wires increases with distance, therefore, in order to lose as litte energy as possible, a high voltage and low amperage is passed through, rather than the inverse."
		""
		"Go back to V=IR, The relationship between our current and resistance would be the inverse of resistance, multiplied by our input voltage. Therefore, applying a high voltage allows for a higher possible current. If we were to increase current instead, a much higher current would be involved, as we fight against our resistance. Not only would this help with saftey in the real world, but it prevents our wires from burning up."
		""
		"Note that this process is especially important because iron wires have the highest parasitic resistance, yet also the longest block reach."
	]
	quest.684CD724E2211165.quest_subtitle: "Establish a small network of powerlines"
	quest.684CD724E2211165.title: "Powerlines!"
