	quest.6DCB2B0EC68ECCFF.title: "Sandworm Showdown"
	quest.6E64FEB176A3779C.quest_desc: [
		"I think you know what a lightbulb does, the perfect asthetic choice for light!"
		"Rated for 120V, will consume/requires 250 mA current. Somewhat self regulating, so you can connect these straight into a 120V source."
		""
		"&oPonder for more details&r"
	]
	quest.6E64FEB176A3779C.quest_subtitle: "Obtain a Lightbulb"
	quest.6E64FEB176A3779C.title: "Edison's Beauty"
	quest.6F10FC61DE4B81D2.quest_desc: [
		"Pneumatic cylinders are pretty much swivel bearings but for linear physics!"
		""
		"      The rotational speed inputted through the bottom increases the speed at which the cylinder actuates, capped at 2 [m/s]."
		"      Power with redstone to actuate. Sadly, analog levels do not change the length the piston extends to yet."
		""
		"{image:minecraft:item/wind_charge width:25 height:25 align:center}"
	]
	quest.6F10FC61DE4B81D2.quest_subtitle: "Obtain a Pneumatic Cylinder"
	quest.6F10FC61DE4B81D2.title: "Linear Physics"
	quest.6FFA30F3DE3897B6.quest_desc: [
		"Cogs are the base of transferring all rotational motion, and they allow for the gear ratio!"
		"There are two cogs, small and large. "
		""
		"Small cogs can be connected in series along one block face, they will inverse the rotation of each cog down the chain, transfering rotational motion against the length of the shaft."
		""
		"Large cogs cannot be connected along one block face, instead, they can change the direction of rotation in the xyz plane, along the minecraft grid. "
		""
		"Together, small and large cogs can be connected across their diagonals to gear ratio- this allows  the player to speed up or slow down the rotation of a contraption or processing item at the expense of [su]"
		""
		"{image:create:block/adjustable_chain_gearshift width:25 height:25 align:center}"
		"{@pagebreak}"
		"Holding [W] on most create mod items will allow the user to engage in a &oponder&r.This shows the player a visible depiction of how to use a item/block without the use of an online wiki. Use this and what you've learned about JEI to complete this task and learn about create!"
	]
	quest.6FFA30F3DE3897B6.quest_subtitle: "Obtain large and small cogwheels, then use them to transfer [su] into [rpm]"
	quest.6FFA30F3DE3897B6.title: "Gearmaster"
